  • Enum Constant Details

    • VERY_GOOD

      public static final Quality VERY_GOOD
      Meets the criterium to a very high degree, having or no relevant need for improvement. This is to be judged in view of the criterium's contribution to the data set's potential overall environmental impact and in comparison to an ideal situation.

    • GOOD

      public static final Quality GOOD
      Meets the criterium to a high degree, having little yet significant need for improvement. This is to be judged in view of the criterium's contribution to the data set's potential overall environmental impact and in comparison to an ideal situation.

    • FAIR

      public static final Quality FAIR
      Meets the criterium to a still sufficient degree, while having the need for improvement. This is to be judged in view of the criterium's contribution to the data set's potential overall environmental impact and in comparison to an ideal situation.

    • POOR

      public static final Quality POOR
      Does not meet the criterium to a sufficient degree, having the need for relevant improvement. This is to be judged in view of the criterium's contribution to the data set's potential overall environmental impact and in comparison to an ideal situation.

    • VERY_POOR

      public static final Quality VERY_POOR
      Does not at all meet the criterium, having the need for very substantial improvement. This is to be judged in view of the criterium's contribution to the data set's potential overall environmental impact and in comparison to an ideal situation.

    • NOT_EVALUATED_UNKNOWN

      public static final Quality NOT_EVALUATED_UNKNOWN
      This criterium was not reviewed or its quality could not be verified.

    • NOT_APPLICABLE

      public static final Quality NOT_APPLICABLE
      This criterium is not applicable to this data set, e.g. its geographical representative can not be evaluated as it is a location-unspecific technology unit process.
